INSERT INTO `headlines` VALUES ('20150627230433', 'samsung_smart_truck.jpg', 'Samsung Introduces New "Safety Truck" Concept', 'Technology opens the doors to many new possibilities. It can \r\nenable us to do the most complicated things such as flying to the \r\nmoon, to more mundane things like automatically opening a door \r\nfor us. Sometimes we get too used to it and we take it for \r\ngranted, but I donâ€™t think we should. Let me explain: as we all \r\nknow driving can be very dangerous. \r\n<br><br>\r\nOne of the most dangerous parts of it is overtaking large trucks \r\non single lane highways, and this in some countries is the largest \r\nsource of accidents. Samsung has used the power of technology \r\nto reduce the number of accidents that occur in these situation. \r\nWatch the video and let us know what you think.\r\n<br><br> <iframe width="80%" height="350" \r\nsrc="http://www.youtube.com/embed/ZetSRWchM4w"> \r\n</iframe> <br><br>	', 'other', '27-Jun-2015', '11:04 PM', 13);
INSERT INTO `headlines` VALUES ('20150628000203', 'bale.jpg', 'Gareth Bale Will Outstay Ronaldo At Real Madrid - John Toshack', 'Ex-Real Madrid coach John Toshack believes Gareth Bale will \r\noutstay Cristiano Ronaldo at the Spanish club.\r\nBale, 25, was the subject of criticism from fans and media as \r\nReal failed to win La Liga and the Champions League.\r\nThe Wales forward was linked with a return to the Premier \r\nLeague but has said he will stay at the Bernabeu.\r\n"My own opinion is that we will probably see, for one reason or \r\nanother, Cristiano move from Madrid before Gareth," Toshack \r\nsaid.<br><br>\r\nForward Ronaldo, 30, has been a Real Madrid player since \r\nsigning from Manchester United for Â£80m in 2009.\r\nBale joined Real from Tottenham for a world-record fee of \r\nÂ£85.3m in 2013, helping the Spanish club claim their 10th \r\nEuropean title in his first season.\r\nThe Welshman scored 22 goals in his debut campaign followed \r\nby 17 in his second. "You do need time to adapt and obviously \r\nfor the money they paid for Bale and at the age that he is, he''s \r\nstill got a lot to do," Toshack added.\r\n<br><br>\r\n"I hope Gareth will get the opportunity to play in an area of the \r\nfield where he can do most damage.\r\n<br><br>\r\n"I''m not so sure wide is Gareth''s best position. I think Cristiano \r\nhas got a bit do with that.\r\n<br><br>\r\n"He was always a number seven, but likes to play left side and I \r\nthink Gareth suffers a bit for that."\r\n<br><br>\r\nToshack, who was Wales manager when Bale made his debut \r\nas a 16-year-old in 2006, had two spells at Real Madrid. The \r\nSpanish side appointed Rafa Benitez as their new coach on 3 \r\nJune.\r\nFormer Liverpool and Chelsea manager Benitez was in Cardiff \r\nrecently to see Bale score in Wales'' 1-0 win over Belgium in a \r\nEuro 2016 qualifier.\r\nEx-Liverpool and Cardiff City striker Toshack now coaches \r\nMoroccan side Wydad Casablanca and believes Benitez is a \r\ngood choice as Carlo Ancelotti''s successor.\r\n"Rafa''s got all the credentials, there''s no question about that," \r\nToshack added.<br><br>\r\n"Rafa was at Madrid at the time I was there, working with the \r\njunior sides.<br><br>\r\n"They''re full on with Benitez now in Spain, in particular the \r\nnewspaper Marca.<br><br>\r\n"Everyday it''s ''Rafa''s going to do this and Rafa''s going to do that'' \r\nbut we just have to wait and see."', 'soccer', '28-Jun-2015', '12:02 AM', 27);
INSERT INTO `headlines` VALUES ('20150628212022', 'ronaldo_depay.jpg', 'Manchester United Legend, Ryan Giggs Compares Memphis \r\nDepay To Cristiano Ronaldo', 'Dutch star Depay''s move to Old Trafford was confirmed earlier \r\nthis \r\nmonth and Giggs thinks he will provide something which has \r\nbeen \r\nmissing since Ronaldo left.<br><br>\r\nRyan Giggs believes Manchester United could finally have found \r\nthe perfect replacement for free-kick specialist Cristiano Ronaldo \r\nin the form of Memphis Depay.\r\n\r\nDepay scored seven of his 22 Eredivisie goals from set-pieces \r\nlast season, and the Dutchman is renowned for his dead ball \r\nabilities - just like Ronaldo was.\r\n\r\nThe Portuguese star netted a number of memorable free-kicks \r\nduring his six-year spell at Old Trafford, and Giggs doesn''t think \r\nhe has been replaced since leaving for Real Madrid in 2009 - \r\nuntil now.\r\n\r\n"One thing we probably have lacked since Cristiano - and Becks \r\n(David Beckham) before him â€“ is free kicks," claims Giggs. "And \r\nit looks like Depay has a great track record from free kicks as \r\nwell.\r\n<br><br> <a \r\nhref="http://www.fab8thproductions.com/pictures/giggs.jpg" \r\ntarget="_blank"> <img \r\nsrc="http://www.fab8thproductions.com/pictures/giggs.jpg" \r\nwidth="90%" height="300"/> </a> <br>Giggs has compared \r\nDepay to \r\nformer Old Trafford favourite Ronaldo.<br><br>	\r\n"Over a season, if you can score more from free-kicks and \r\ncorners it adds up and makes a real difference in winning games. \r\nSo, no pressureâ€¦ but hopefully he''ll score 10 free kicks every \r\nyear!"\r\n\r\nGiggs also believes that Depay has chosen the best place to \r\ndevelop his career, due to the club''s supporters'' patience with \r\nyoung players.\r\n\r\nThe Welshman added: "Old Trafford is the right stage for a \r\nplayer like him, because if you try things that don''t come off the \r\nfans will stay behind you. You''re at a club where they want you to \r\ndo things off the cuff, to entertain them."\r\n\r\nDepay will finalise his move from PSV when the summer transfer \r\nwindow officially opens at midnight on Wednesday 1 July.', 'soccer', '28-Jun-2015', '09:20 PM', 12);
INSERT INTO `headlines` VALUES ('20150628222041', 'de_gea.jpg', 'De Gea May Be Forced To See Out Contract At Man Utd', 'Manchester United goalkeeper David de Gea may be forced to \r\nsee out the final year of his contract at Old Trafford with Real \r\nMadrid refusing to meet the Old Trafford club''s Â£20million asking \r\nprice.\r\nThe two European heavyweights are refusing to budge on their \r\ndifferent valuation of de Gea who only has a year left on his \r\nUnited contract.\r\nAnd the stand-off means there is a very real possibility of the 24-\r\nyear-old Spaniard having to wait another 12 months before \r\nreturning ''home'' despite the move being considered a done deal \r\na few weeks ago.<br><br>\r\nMadrid, with new manager Rafa Benitez at the helm, are \r\nsteadfast that they will not give United more than Â£13m given \r\nthat they can get him for nothing in a year''s time.\r\nBut United, who are already committed to a big summer of \r\nspending on the likes of Morgan Schneiderlin, say they won''t let \r\nDe Gea go for that amount and have to buy a replacement \r\ngoalkeeper to compete with Victor Valdes.\r\nThe impasse leaves manager Louis van Gaal in an awkward \r\nposition of trying to coax top performances out of De Gea whose \r\ngirlfriend wants to return to Spain immediately.\r\n<br><br> <a \r\nhref="http://www.fab8thproductions.com/pictures/degea_casillas.j\r\npg" target="_blank"> <img \r\nsrc="http://www.fab8thproductions.com/pictures/degea_casillas.j\r\npg" width="90%" height="330"/> </a><br>De Gea and Casillas \r\non National Team Duty <br><br>.\r\nUnited signed De Gea from Atletico Madrid for a record Â£18m in \r\n2011 as their replacement for Edwin van der Sar and after a \r\nshaky start, he has gone on to win the league title at Old Trafford \r\nand is considered one of the best goalkeepers in the Premier \r\nLeague.<br><br>\r\nHaving already signed Dutch winger Memphis Depay for Â£25m, \r\nvan Gaal is believed to be close to adding Schneiderlin to his \r\nsquad from Southampton and is still looking for a top-class right-\r\nback, centre-half and striker.\r\n	', 'soccer', '28-Jun-2015', '10:20 PM', 9);
INSERT INTO `headlines` VALUES ('20150628223150', 'buhari.jpg', 'Buhari: Ekweremadu as Sarakiâ€™s deputy unacceptable', 'For President Muhammadu Buhari, the emergence of a Peoples \r\nDemocratic Party (PDP) member as deputy Senate President in \r\nthe current dispensation is nothing short of a setback for his \r\nadministration.\r\nHe is irked that some members of his own party, All Progressives \r\nCongress (APC), conceded the position to Ike Ekweremadu \r\nwhen the PDP never gave that much all through its 16 years in \r\npower between 1999 and last May.<br><br>\r\n\r\nBut he is optimistic that the APC will overcome the setback.\r\nPresident Buhari made his feelings known at a meeting with a \r\ndelegation of the   Unity Forum at the Aso Rock Villa on Friday \r\nnight.\r\nThe forum is the group of senators backing Dr. Ahmed Lawan, \r\nthe APC anointed candidate for the Senate Presidency.<br><br>\r\n\r\nBuhari, at the meeting, reportedly pleaded for the understanding \r\nof APC Senators as the party explores reconciliation options.\r\nHowever, the majority of the APC governors and state chairmen \r\nof the party are insisting that Senate President Bukola Saraki \r\nand House of Reps Speaker Yakubu Dogara comply with the \r\npartyâ€™s directive on the choice of principal officers of the National \r\nAssembly.<br><br>\r\n\r\nThe APC governors and state chairmen are encouraging the \r\nleadership of the party to enforce discipline to prevent it from \r\ncollapsing.\r\nSome party leaders, it was gathered, have proposed a former \r\nNational Chairman of the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP), Chief \r\nAudu Ogbeh, as chairman of the APC Disciplinary Committee to \r\nlook into allegations of anti-party activities against some \r\nmembers.<br><br>\r\n\r\nPresident Buhari at the Friday meeting was said to have said \r\nthere was no reason for the party to be divided over who heads \r\nthe National Assembly.<br><br>\r\n\r\nâ€œThe President gave us audience and admitted that the \r\ndevelopment in the Senate was a setback but he expressed \r\nconfidence that APC will overcome it,â€ a source at the meeting \r\nsaid.<br><br>\r\n\r\nâ€œHe said there was no basis for the split among APC Senators \r\nwhich led to the concession of the Office of Deputy President of \r\nthe Senate to the PDP. He said PDP did not give the opposition \r\nsuch an opportunity in its 16 years in power.<br><br>\r\n\r\nâ€œBuhari told Lawan and others not to take the law into their hands \r\nas the leaders of the party explore reconciliation options. He said \r\npeace and the survival of the nationâ€™s democracy should be \r\nparamount more than any other thing.â€<br><br> <a \r\nhref="http://www.fab8thproductions.com/pictures/buhari_in_office\r\n.JPG" target="_blank"> <img \r\nsrc="http://www.fab8thproductions.com/pictures/buhari_in_office.\r\nJPG" width="90%" height="330"/> </a><br>President Buhari in \r\nthe Presidential Office. <br><br>	\r\n\r\nAsked to assess the Presidentâ€™s mood at the session, the source \r\nadded: â€œHe was not happy about the development in the Senate \r\nbut he was hopeful that the situation is redeemable if some \r\nleaders can sacrifice their ambitions for the survival of APC and \r\nhis administration.â€<br><br>\r\n\r\nAnother source said: â€œThe session was cordial and reassuring. \r\nThe President interacted with us individually and even had time \r\nto crack jokes with us before we receded into the business of the \r\nday".<br><br>\r\n\r\n\r\nâ€œAs for the Lawan group, it was Senator Barnabas Gemade who \r\nspoke on behalf of the 51 aggrieved Senators".<br><br>\r\n\r\nâ€œGemade said the Unity Forum is after justice since its members \r\nhave demonstrated their faith in APC leadership and having \r\nbeen loyal to the party to a fault".<br><br>\r\n\r\nâ€œGemade restated the six demands of the group and the need to \r\nprevail on Saraki and Dogara to abide by the directive of the \r\nparty on the nominees for principal offices in the Senate and \r\nHouse of Representatives.â€<br><br>\r\n\r\nThe source quoted Gemade as saying: â€œWhen the Vice \r\nPresident, Prof. Yemi Osinbajo called a meeting to address the \r\nlooming challenge, it was only our group that responded; we \r\nwere the only group which participated in the partyâ€™s straw poll \r\nand even on June 9, we deferred to the partyâ€™s invitation to a \r\nmeeting at the International Conference Centre.<br><br>\r\n\r\nâ€œBefore anybody knew it, the Like Minds went for the \r\ninauguration of the Senate and elected Saraki".<br><br>\r\n\r\nâ€œWe have proved our unflinching loyalty to the party. This is the \r\ntime for the party to assert itself and enforce discipline or else \r\nmembers will continue to take the leadership of the party for \r\ngranted.â€<br><br>\r\n\r\nAhead of the meeting of the National Executive Committee of the \r\nAPC on Tuesday, there were indications last night that the \r\ngovernors elected on the platform of the party and state \r\nchairmen are pushing for Dr. Saraki and Hon. Dogara to comply \r\nwith the partyâ€™s directive on the choice of principal officers of the \r\nNational Assembly.\r\n\r\nThey said they will no longer tolerate the defiance of the party by \r\nthe two leaders.<br>\r\nA member of the NWC said: â€œWe are expecting a stormy session \r\non Tuesday. Saraki and Dogara will have to choose between \r\nloyalty to the party or self-serving agenda.<br><br>\r\n\r\nâ€œThe only condition for moving forward is for these leaders to \r\naccept the list sent to them by the National Chairman of APC, \r\nChief John Odigie-Oyegun".<br><br>\r\n\r\nThose  recommended by the APC for Senate positions are \r\n<br>Sen. Ahmed  Lawan(Majority Leader)-North-East; <br>Prof. \r\nSola Adeyeye( Chief Whip)â€”South-West; <br>Sen. George \r\nAkume( Deputy Majority Leader)â€”North-Central; <br>Sen. Abu \r\nIbrahim(Deputy Chief Whip)â€”North-West.<br><br>\r\n\r\nThe partyâ€™s list for the 8th House of Representatives  is as \r\nfollows:  Hon. Femi Gbajabiamila( House Leader)--South-West; \r\n<br>Hon. Alhassan Ado Doguwa( Deputy House Leader)â€”\r\nNorth-West; <br>Hon. M. T. Monguno( Chief Whip)â€”North-East; \r\n<br>Hon. Pally Iriase( Deputy Chief Whip)â€”South-South.<br>\r\n<br>\r\n\r\nIt was gathered that if Saraki and Dogara refused to respect the \r\npartyâ€™s list, APC may resort to sanctions.<br>\r\nIt was learnt that some forces in the party are pushing for the \r\nappointment of a former National Chairman of PDP, Chief Audu \r\nOgbeh as the head of the partyâ€™s Disciplinary Committee.\r\n\r\nA top member of the party said: â€œThere is no doubt that Ogbeh is \r\nwell grounded in party politics and he is a disciplinarian.  We are \r\nthinking of him to assist in unraveling the anti-party activities in \r\nthe Senate and the House.â€', 'politics', '28-Jun-2015', '10:31 PM', 9);
INSERT INTO `headlines` VALUES ('20150628225134', 'frmi_adesina.jpg', 'Cleaning PDPâ€™s mess requires painstaking planning â€“ Presidency', 'The Presidency on Sunday said cleaning the mess left behind by \r\nthe Peoples Democratic Party, especially the immediate past \r\nadministration, requires scrupulous and painstaking planning.\r\n<br>\r\nThe Special Adviser to the President on Media and Publicity, Mr. \r\nFemi Adesina, said this in a statement made available to \r\njournalists in Abuja.\r\n<br>\r\nAdesina was reacting to a statement by the National Publicity \r\nSecretary of the PDP, Chief Olisa Metuh, in which he described \r\nthe last 30 days under President Muhammadu Buhari as a period \r\nof all motion and no movement.<br><br>\r\n\r\nThe presidential spokesman said across all sectors, national life \r\nwas devalued under the PDP and it would take meticulousness \r\nand sure-footedness to repair all the breaches.\r\n<br>\r\nHe said, â€œThe Buhari administration is naturally contemplative \r\nbecause there was absolutely no rhyme or reason to the way \r\nPDP ran the country, particularly in the immediate past \r\ndispensation.<br><br>\r\n\r\nâ€œThat is why the Augean Stable is being cleaned now, and it \r\nrequires scrupulous and painstaking planning.\r\n<br><br>\r\nâ€œAcross all sectors, our national life was devalued, and it takes \r\nmeticulousness and sure-footedness to repair all the breaches. \r\nThis, the Buhari administration will deliver.â€\r\n<br><br>\r\nHe described the PDPâ€™s 30 days appraisal of the Buhari \r\nadministration as amusing.\r\n\r\nAdesina said while the party wanted Nigerians to join hands in \r\nprayers for the government so that things would begin to move, it \r\ndid not know that Nigerians had long formed such coalition.\r\n\r\nHe said Nigerians were hand in hand, and that was what gave \r\nvictory to Buhari in the March 28, 2015 poll.\r\n\r\nHe said they had teamed up to uproot an administration that had \r\nbrought the country to her knees, and was about to tip her off the \r\nprecipice, adding that they also resolved that never would they \r\nallow any government to divide them along regional, religious \r\nand ethnic fault lines again.\r\n<br><br>\r\nThe presidential spokesman also described as â€œdÃ©jÃ  vu,â€ a \r\nsituation where Metuh claimed that people around the President \r\nwere conniving with bureaucrats to syphon money from the \r\ntreasury.\r\n\r\nHe said such situation was the pastime of the immediate past \r\nadministration.\r\n\r\nHe added that the enormity of the sleaze will be evident when \r\nstolen money, to the tune of billions of dollars, is recovered, and \r\nreturned to the national treasury soon.\r\n<br><br>\r\nâ€œIn the process of time, after all that is being planned by the \r\ncurrent administration has matured, and bearing fruits, Nigerians \r\nwill be able to determine who is serving them acceptably, and \r\nwho has taken them for a ride. It is just a matter of time.\r\n<br><br>\r\nâ€œMeanwhile, Metuh and his masters can only rue the missed \r\nopportunities to make salutary impact on the lives of Nigerians. \r\nThey have a long road of regrets to travel,â€ Adesina concluded.', 'politics', '28-Jun-2015', '10:51 PM', 8);
INSERT INTO `headlines` VALUES ('20150803231155', 'tega.jpg', 'Esabunor Tega, Missing 18 year old Unilag Student Has Been \r\nFound', 'About 4 days ago, news broke out that an 18 year old student of \r\nthe Mechanical Engineering department in the University had \r\ngone missing. It soon gained traction all through social media \r\nand everyone started sharing this as broadcasts to all they knew. \r\n<br><br>A young lady by the name Esabunor Bithiah made a \r\ntweet claiming the missing Tega was her brother as shown \r\nbelow:\r\n<blockquote class="twitter-tweet" lang="en"><p lang="en" \r\ndir="ltr">My brother tega is missing please contact me with any \r\ninformation <a \r\nhref="http://t.co/y1LfdvtjWp">pic.twitter.com/y1LfdvtjWp</a>\r\n</p>&mdash; bithiah esabunor (@bithiahnukie) <a \r\nhref="https://twitter.com/bithiahnukie/status/62792270553957990\r\n5">August 2, 2015</a></blockquote>\r\n<script async src="//platform.twitter.com/widgets.js" charset="utf-\r\n8"></script>\r\n<br>\r\n<blockquote class="twitter-tweet" lang="en"><p lang="und" \r\ndir="ltr"><a href="https://twitter.com/hashtag/helpfindmybrother?\r\nsrc=hash">#helpfindmybrother</a> <a \r\nhref="http://t.co/SGoo2XPjki">pic.twitter.com/SGoo2XPjki</a>\r\n</p>&mdash; bithiah esabunor (@bithiahnukie) <a \r\nhref="https://twitter.com/bithiahnukie/status/62792707155415040\r\n0">August 2, 2015</a></blockquote>\r\n<script async src="//platform.twitter.com/widgets.js" charset="utf-\r\n8"></script>\r\n<br>\r\nA few minutes ago, it was gathered that the missing Tega had \r\nfinally returned home. Although not fully confirmed, Esabunor \r\nBithiah once again claims that her brother had returned home.\r\n<br>\r\n<blockquote class="twitter-tweet" lang="en"><p lang="en" \r\ndir="ltr">The fact that I have seen my brother with my own two \r\neyes at home is proof that Jehovah God is alive.</p>&mdash; \r\nbithiah esabunor (@bithiahnukie) <a \r\nhref="https://twitter.com/bithiahnukie/status/62830660636789555\r\n2">August 3, 2015</a></blockquote>\r\n<script async src="//platform.twitter.com/widgets.js" charset="utf-\r\n8"></script>\r\n<br>\r\n<blockquote class="twitter-tweet" lang="en"><p lang="und" \r\ndir="ltr"><a href="https://twitter.com/hashtag/mybrotherisback?\r\nsrc=hash">#mybrotherisback</a></p>&mdash; bithiah esabunor \r\n(@bithiahnukie) <a \r\nhref="https://twitter.com/bithiahnukie/status/62830670104590745\r\n7">August 3, 2015</a></blockquote>\r\n<script async src="//platform.twitter.com/widgets.js" charset="utf-\r\n8"></script>\r\n<br>\r\n<blockquote class="twitter-tweet" lang="en"><p lang="und" \r\ndir="ltr"><a href="https://twitter.com/hashtag/TegaIsBack?\r\nsrc=hash">#TegaIsBack</a></p>&mdash; bithiah esabunor \r\n(@bithiahnukie) <a \r\nhref="https://twitter.com/bithiahnukie/status/62830679670959309\r\n2">August 3, 2015</a></blockquote>\r\n<script async src="//platform.twitter.com/widgets.js" charset="utf-\r\n8"></script>\r\n<br>', 'other', '03-Aug-2015', '11:11 PM', 7);
INSERT INTO `headlines` VALUES ('20151212075403', '5.jpg', '5 Artistes\r\nWho Failed\r\nTo Release\r\nAn Album\r\nIn 2015', 'In 2015, a\r\nlot of\r\nactivities\r\nhappened\r\nin the\r\never\r\ngrowing\r\nNigerian\r\nmusic\r\nindustry\r\nincluding\r\nthe\r\nrelease of\r\nanticipated albums.\r\nNaij.comâ€™s\r\nMichael\r\nAbimboye\r\ntakes a\r\nlook at 5\r\nartistes\r\nwho should\r\nhave\r\nrelease an\r\nalbum in\r\n2015 but\r\nfailed to.\r\n<br>\r\n\r\n<br>\r\n\r\nDBANJ\r\n\r\n<br>\r\nEja Nla as\r\nhe is now\r\ncalled,\r\nDâ€™banj yet\r\nagain\r\nfailed to\r\nrelease\r\nhis now\r\nperhaps\r\nless\r\nanticipated fourth\r\nstudio\r\nalbum.\r\n <br><br>\r\n<a\r\nhref="http://www.fab8thproductions.com/pictures/dbanj.jpg"\r\ntarget="_blank">\r\n<img\r\nsrc="http://www.fab8thproductions.com/pictures/dbanj.jpg"\r\nwidth="90%" height="330"/>\r\n</a>\r\n<br><br>\r\n\r\nThe singer\r\nhowever\r\nreleased\r\nan EP in\r\n2015 which\r\ngot little\r\nor no\r\nattention\r\nfrom fans,\r\ncritics\r\nand all.\r\nSince\r\nsplitting\r\nfrom his\r\nerstwhile\r\nbusiness\r\npartner\r\nand music\r\nproducer\r\nDonjazzy,\r\nDâ€™banj has\r\nfailed to\r\nmaintain\r\nor build\r\nupon the\r\nmusic\r\nheight he\r\nattained\r\nwhile at\r\nMoâ€™hits\r\nrecords.\r\nAs a\r\nmatter of\r\nfact, his\r\nranking\r\nhas\r\ndropped in\r\nthe\r\nNigeria\r\nmusic\r\nscene.\r\n\r\nDâ€™banjâ€™s\r\ninability\r\nto record\r\na hit song\r\nsince the\r\n2012\r\nOliver\r\nTwist is\r\nbelieved\r\nto be one\r\nfactor\r\nworking\r\nagainst\r\nthe\r\nrelease of\r\nthe much\r\nanticipated album.\r\n<br>\r\n\r\n<br>\r\nK-SWITCH\r\n<br>\r\n\r\n<br><br>\r\n<a\r\nhref="http://www.fab8thproductions.com/pictures/kswitch.jpg"\r\ntarget="_blank">\r\n<img\r\nsrc="http://www.fab8thproductions.com/pictures/kswitch.jpg"\r\nwidth="90%" height="330"/>\r\n</a>\r\n<br><br>\r\n\r\nK-swtichâ€™s\r\ncareer has\r\ncontinued\r\nto stay in\r\nthe\r\nbackground\r\nsince his\r\ndays at\r\nMoâ€™hits\r\nrecords.\r\nWhile his\r\nfellow\r\nlowkey\r\nact,\r\nDâ€™Prince\r\nhas\r\nreleased\r\nhis debut\r\nalbum and\r\nhit\r\nsingles,\r\nK-switch\r\nonly\r\nmanaged to\r\nshow a\r\nglimpse of\r\nthe stuff\r\nhe is made\r\nof with\r\nhis 2013\r\nhit, Obimo\r\nand failed\r\nto\r\ncapitalize\r\non the\r\nsuccess of\r\nthe song.\r\nHe was\r\npractically inactive\r\nin 2015\r\nalso. <br>\r\n\r\n<br>\r\nDAVIDO\r\n\r\n<br><br>\r\n<a\r\nhref="http://www.fab8thproductions.com/pictures/davido.jpg"\r\ntarget="_blank">\r\n<img\r\nsrc="http://www.fab8thproductions.com/pictures/davido.jpg"\r\nwidth="90%" height="330"/>\r\n</a>\r\n<br><br>\r\nWith hit\r\nupon hit\r\nsongs,\r\nsold out\r\nconcerts\r\nin some\r\nAfrican\r\ncountries\r\ncoupled\r\nwith\r\ninternational\r\ncollaboration\r\nHKN lead\r\nact,\r\nDavido had\r\na\r\nsuccessful\r\nyear but\r\nrefused to\r\nconsolidate on\r\nthese\r\ngains by\r\nnot\r\nreleasing\r\nhis\r\nsophomore\r\nalbum.\r\nSources\r\nwithin HKN\r\ncamp said\r\nthe delay\r\nin the\r\nrelease of\r\nthe album\r\nwas due to\r\nan\r\ninternational\r\ndistribution\r\ndeal. He\r\nhad\r\npromised\r\non several\r\noccasions\r\nto release\r\nthe album\r\ntitled\r\nBaddest in\r\n2015.<br>\r\n\r\n<br>\r\nWIZKID<br>\r\n\r\n<br><br>\r\n<a\r\nhref="http://www.fab8thproductions.com/pictures/wizzy.jpg"\r\ntarget="_blank">\r\n<img\r\nsrc="http://www.fab8thproductions.com/pictures/wizzy.jpg"\r\nwidth="90%" height="330"/>\r\n</a>\r\n<br><br>\r\nWith a\r\nmonster\r\nhit song\r\nlike\r\nOjuelegba\r\nwhich\r\nlater got\r\nthe\r\nattention\r\nof hottest\r\nrapper in\r\nworld,\r\nDrake,\r\nWizkid\r\nfailed to\r\nrelease\r\nhis third\r\nstudio\r\nalbum. He\r\nhowever\r\nmaintained\r\nhis\r\nchampion\r\non the\r\nNigeria\r\nand\r\nAfrican\r\nmusic\r\nscene\r\nchurning\r\nout hits\r\nand\r\njumping\r\ncollaborations.\r\nHe also\r\nhad sold\r\nout\r\nconcerts\r\nas well as\r\nmove to\r\nGlo from\r\nMTN.<br>\r\n\r\n<br>\r\n\r\nLIL KESH\r\n<br>\r\n\r\n<br><br>\r\n<a\r\nhref="http://www.fab8thproductions.com/pictures/lil_kesh.jpg"\r\ntarget="_blank">\r\n<img\r\nsrc="http://www.fab8thproductions.com/pictures/lil_kesh.jpg"\r\nwidth="90%" height="330"/>\r\n</a>\r\n<br><br>\r\n\r\nYBNL star\r\nfailed to\r\njump on\r\nthe\r\nopportunity of\r\nreleasing\r\nsome of\r\nthe club\r\nbangers of\r\n2015 to\r\nrelease\r\nhis debut\r\nalbum.\r\nWith songs\r\nlike\r\nEfejoku,\r\nGbese ,\r\nLadi, Lil\r\nKesh would\r\nhave\r\nreleased\r\nhis debut\r\nbut he let\r\nhis boss,\r\nOlamide\r\nmake\r\nhistory\r\nwith 5\r\nalbums in\r\n5 years.\r\n\r\n', 'entertainment', '12-Dec-2015', '07:54 AM', 3);
INSERT INTO `headlines` VALUES ('20151212093706', 'm2.jpg', 'Nollywood\r\nactress,\r\nMercy\r\nJohnson\r\nwelcomes\r\n3rd\r\nchild...', 'Nigerian\r\nactress,\r\nMercy\r\nJohnson\r\nhas\r\nwelcomed\r\nher 3rd\r\nchild, a\r\nbaby girl\r\non\r\nDecember\r\n11, 2015.\r\nThe baby\r\nwas born\r\nat about\r\n9:00 pm at\r\nUniversity\r\nOf\r\nMaryland\r\n(Saint\r\nJoseph),\r\nUnited\r\nStates Of\r\nAmerica,\r\nthe same\r\nhospital\r\nwhere she\r\ngave birth\r\nto her\r\nfirst two\r\nkids. <br>\r\n <br><br>\r\n<a\r\nhref="http://www.fab8thproductions.com/pictures/m4.jpg"\r\ntarget="_blank">\r\n<img\r\nsrc="http://www.fab8thproductions.com/pictures/m4.jpg"\r\nwidth="90%" height="330"/>\r\n</a>\r\n<br><br>\r\n\r\nHer hubby,\r\nPrince\r\nOkojie was\r\nwith her\r\nat the\r\nhospital\r\nat the\r\ntime of\r\nthe\r\ndelivery\r\nof their\r\n3rd child.\r\nMercy\r\nJohnson,\r\nnow a\r\nmother of\r\n3,\r\nwelcomed\r\nher second\r\nson, Henry\r\non\r\nWednesday,\r\nOctober\r\n15, 2014,\r\nwhile her\r\nfirst\r\nchild,\r\nPurity was\r\nborn in\r\nDecember\r\n2012....\r\n<br><br>\r\n<a\r\nhref="http://www.fab8thproductions.com/pictures/mercy_1.jpg"\r\ntarget="_blank">\r\n<img\r\nsrc="http://www.fab8thproductions.com/pictures/mercy_1.jpg"\r\nwidth="90%" height="330"/>\r\n</a>\r\n<br><br>\r\n\r\n Follow\r\nus:\r\n@Fab8thprod1\r\non Twitter\r\nand\r\nInstagram\r\n |\r\nFab8thproductions\r\non\r\nFacebook', 'entertainment', '12-Dec-2015', '09:37 AM', 5);
INSERT INTO `headlines` VALUES ('20151213172247', 'tt.jpg', 'Keep your\r\nHome\r\nAffairs to\r\nYourself,\r\nNever\r\nEntertain\r\nFriends â€“\r\nTonto\r\nDikeh\r\nWarns ', 'Popular\r\nNollywood\r\nactress,\r\nTonto\r\nDikeh-Churchill,\r\nhas\r\nadvised\r\nher fans\r\nand\r\ncolleagues\r\nto keep\r\ntheir\r\nrelationship\r\nand home\r\nprivate.<br>\r\n<br>\r\n\r\nTonto\r\nshared a\r\npicture of\r\nHollywood\r\ncouples\r\nthat have\r\nbeen\r\ntogether\r\nfor 32\r\nyears and\r\nhas\r\nexperienced the\r\nboth sides\r\nof\r\nmarriage.\r\nShe\r\ncaptioned;<br>\r\n<br>\r\n\r\nâ€œMy goal\r\nis not to\r\nlavish\r\nmoney,\r\nwalk the\r\nstreets\r\nlike a\r\nQueen I\r\ntruly am,\r\nfeeling\r\nstuck up.\r\nI married\r\nright,\r\nbrag about\r\nwhere I am\r\nnow and\r\nyou are\r\nnot but be\r\na victor\r\nin what I\r\nhold dear\r\n(my home).\r\nYours or\r\nours can\r\nbe a part\r\nof history\r\ntoo and a\r\ngreat\r\ninspiration to\r\nothers.<br>\r\n<br>\r\n\r\nâ€œElegance\r\nis when\r\nthe inside\r\nis as\r\nbeautiful\r\nas the\r\noutside.\r\nKeep your\r\ndirty and\r\nclean\r\nlinens to\r\nyourself\r\nand never\r\nlet\r\nfriends\r\nhave a say\r\nin your\r\nhome. If\r\nyou can\r\nnever\r\nentertain\r\nfriends in\r\nyour home,\r\nmeet\r\nelsewhere.\r\nNow my\r\nfriend is\r\nwisdom. I\r\ntell\r\nmyself I\r\nrefuse to\r\nbe one of\r\nthe broken\r\nones; I\r\ncanâ€™t do\r\nit alone\r\nthat is\r\nwhy I\r\ninvited my\r\nthree\r\ngreatest\r\nlovers The\r\nFather,\r\nSon and\r\nthe Holy\r\nSpirit.â€\r\n<br>\r\n<br>\r\n\r\nThe\r\nactress\r\nhad her\r\nwedding to\r\nChurchill\r\nOlakulne\r\nOladunni\r\nthis year\r\nin Port\r\nHarcourt,\r\nRivers\r\nState and\r\nhas since\r\nkept her\r\nhome from\r\nthe public\r\nwhile she\r\ngoes about\r\nusing her\r\nsocial\r\nmedia page\r\nto pray\r\nand adore\r\nher\r\nhusband.<br>', 'entertainment', '13-Dec-2015', '05:22 PM', 4);
INSERT INTO `headlines` VALUES ('20151213180622', 'saint_obi.jpg', 'I Never\r\nBought Car\r\nFor\r\nN48mâ€”Saint\r\nObi', 'Veteran\r\nNollywood\r\nactor,\r\nSaint Obi\r\n?has\r\nsquealed\r\nwhat he\r\nhas been\r\nup to\r\nsince his\r\nface\r\nbecame\r\nless\r\nfrequent\r\non\r\ntelevision\r\nscreens.<br>\r\n<br>\r\n\r\nThe former\r\nlover-boy\r\nactor also\r\ndisclosed\r\nthat he\r\nhas\r\nstarted a\r\nrecord\r\nlabel and\r\nwill be\r\ndishing\r\nout fresh\r\nsongs with\r\ntwo other\r\nguys from\r\nthe group,\r\npointing\r\nout that\r\nhe is now\r\ninto the\r\nmusic\r\nworld.<br>\r\n<br>\r\n\r\nHowever,\r\nhe denied\r\nacquiring\r\na Mercedes\r\nG-Wagon\r\nworth\r\nN48m. The\r\nactor said\r\ninstead of\r\nlavishing\r\nsuch an\r\namount on\r\nmaterial\r\nthings, he\r\nwill\r\nrather put\r\nit into\r\ncharity or\r\ninvesting\r\nin\r\npeople.<br>\r\n<br>\r\n\r\nâ€œI am not\r\na perfect\r\nbeing but\r\nI am very\r\ndistant\r\nfrom those\r\nthings\r\nwritten or\r\nadduced to\r\nmy person.\r\nAn\r\nexample, I\r\nnever\r\nbought any\r\nG-Wagon\r\nvalued at\r\nM48million.<br>\r\n<br>\r\n\r\nâ€œThe real\r\nme is a\r\nvery\r\nselfless\r\nperson who\r\nwill share\r\nmy last\r\nN100 with\r\nthe needy;\r\nwho is\r\nconstantly\r\nthinking\r\nof ways to\r\nimpact\r\npositively\r\non other\r\npeople and\r\nsociety,\r\nat large.\r\nI donâ€™t\r\nlike\r\ntalking\r\nmuch;\r\nrather I\r\nlet my\r\nworks do\r\nmy\r\ntalking. I\r\nbelieve\r\nthat\r\ncharity,\r\njust like\r\nbeing a\r\nfine\r\nperson\r\nmust start\r\nfrom\r\ninward;\r\nhence if\r\nyou visit\r\nmy\r\nvillage,\r\nUmuezealaeze\r\nAlaenyi,\r\nOgwa in\r\nMbaitoli\r\nLGA of Imo\r\nState, I\r\nhave done\r\nmy little\r\nbit to\r\nhelp my\r\npeople but\r\nmore\r\nimportantly inspire\r\na new\r\nvision,"\r\nSaint Obi\r\nsaid in an\r\ninterview.<br>\r\n<br>\r\n\r\nHe also\r\nsaid,\r\nâ€œThrough\r\nthe Grace\r\nof God\r\nAlmighty,\r\nI was able\r\nto destroy\r\n2 big\r\nshrines in\r\nmy\r\nvillage,\r\nsunk\r\nboreholes,\r\ndid road\r\nrepairs,\r\nempower\r\nthe young\r\nand\r\nold.<br>\r\n<br>\r\n\r\nâ€œMy\r\nactions\r\nare not\r\nlimited to\r\nmy\r\nvillage;\r\nin the\r\ncities, I\r\nam also\r\nconstantly\r\npreaching\r\nagainst\r\nthe Osu\r\nsyndrome,\r\ncrime,\r\npoor\r\nmorals,\r\nreligious\r\nand ethnic\r\nbigotry,\r\nthe need\r\nto for\r\neducation,\r\namongst\r\nothers;\r\nitâ€™s\r\npossible\r\nto change\r\nthe world\r\nand\r\nNigeria if\r\nwe only\r\ntry.â€<br>\r\n<br>\r\nMore\r\nHeadlines\r\nDo you\r\nhave a\r\nstory/gist\r\nfor\r\npublication?\r\nPlease\r\nemail it\r\nto\r\nfab8thproductions@gmail.com\r\n\r\n', 'entertainment', '13-Dec-2015', '06:06 PM', 9);
INSERT INTO `headlines` VALUES ('20151213181415', 'lizzy.jpg', 'I''m not\r\nPsychologically\r\nReady for\r\nMarriageâ€¦Actress,\r\nLizzy Gold\r\n', 'Nollywood\r\nactress,\r\nLizzy Gold\r\nOnuwaje,\r\nis\r\ncurrently\r\nnot happy\r\nwith the\r\nway some\r\npeople\r\nhave\r\nreceived\r\nher since\r\nputting to\r\nbed about\r\na month\r\nago.<br>\r\n<br>\r\n\r\nAccording\r\nto the\r\nactress,\r\nrumours\r\nhave been\r\ncirculating that\r\nshe got\r\npregnant\r\nfor a\r\nmarried\r\nman and\r\nshe has\r\nbeen\r\nreceiving\r\nall sortsâ€™\r\nmails\r\nregarding\r\nthe\r\npaternity\r\nof the\r\nchild.<br>\r\n<br>\r\n\r\nFor those\r\nwho care\r\nto listen,\r\nshe\r\nexplained\r\nthat the\r\nfather of\r\nher child\r\nis still\r\nsingle and\r\nnot\r\nmarried as\r\nwidely\r\nspeculated.<br>\r\n<br>\r\n\r\nShe stated\r\nthat she\r\nhas\r\naccepted\r\nthe way\r\nthings\r\nhave\r\nturned out\r\nfor her\r\nsince she\r\npersonally\r\nchose the\r\nway things\r\nshould go\r\nfor her\r\nand would\r\nnot like\r\npeople\r\ncoming to\r\nmeddle in\r\nher\r\naffairs.\r\nIn her\r\nwords,\r\nâ€œRumours\r\nis always\r\nsweet to\r\npaddle in\r\na canoe by\r\nsome\r\npeeps,\r\ncontinue\r\npaddling d\r\ncanoe\r\nuntil you\r\ngo hit\r\nrock con\r\nbreak your\r\nneck join\r\n(laughs).\r\nI was\r\nraised in\r\na\r\nChristian\r\nhome, and\r\nI will\r\nnever come\r\nin between\r\nsomeone\r\nelseâ€™s\r\nhome for\r\nthose\r\ncurious\r\nlovers\r\nbombarding\r\nmy emails\r\nwith\r\nquestions.<br>\r\n<br>\r\n\r\nâ€œMy baby\r\ndaddy is\r\nas single\r\nas f*ck!\r\nand I am\r\nas real as\r\nf*ck I nor\r\nsabi\r\npretend\r\nfor those\r\nwho know\r\nme, if I\r\nlove you I\r\nlove you\r\nif I don''t\r\nlove you,\r\ntrust me I\r\nnor go\r\nsend you.\r\nDey say\r\nmake your\r\nbed the\r\nway you\r\nchoose to\r\nsleep on\r\nit, na ma\r\nbed I dey\r\nmake so,\r\ngo and\r\nmake\r\nyours.â€<br>\r\n<br>\r\n\r\nLizzy also\r\ndisclosed\r\nthat she\r\nmight be\r\nsingle but\r\nshe is not\r\nsearching\r\nfor a man\r\nnow\r\nbecause\r\nshe is not\r\npsychologically\r\nready for\r\nmarriage.\r\n"Single\r\nbut not\r\nsearching,\r\nnot\r\npsychologically\r\nready for\r\nmarriage\r\nnow for\r\nthose\r\ncurious\r\nfriends. I\r\nlove my\r\nlife."<br>\r\n<br>', 'entertainment', '13-Dec-2015', '06:14 PM', 7);

